Algorithm 1 Training   
1: Input: dataset $D=\{(Z_{i},u_{i})\}_{i\in M}$ , where $M$ refers to the number of data points in $D$ , $Z_{i}$ is   
composed of $x_{i}$ and $h_{i}$ , initial model parameter $\theta$ , learning rate $\eta$ , step schedule $\mathcal{N}(\cdot)$ , EMA   
decay rate schedule $\mu(\cdot)$ , $\theta^{-}\gets\theta$ and $k\leftarrow0$ ;   
2: repeat   
3: Sample $z,u\sim D$ , and $n\sim\mathcal{U}[1,N(k)-1]$ ;   
4: Decompose $z$ into $x$ and $h$ ;   
5: Sample $\epsilon_{v}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,I)$ for $v\in\{x,h\}$ ;   
6: Subtract center of gravity from $\epsilon_{x}$ ;   
7: Define $f_{\theta}^{n,v}\gets f_{\theta}(v+t_{n}\cdot\epsilon_{v},t_{n}|u)$ for $v\in\{x,h\}$ ;   
8: $\begin{array}{r}{L(\theta,\theta^{-})\gets\sum_{v\in\{x,h\}}\mathbf{MSE}(f_{\theta}^{n+1,v},f_{\theta}^{n,v})}\end{array}$ ;   
9: $\theta\leftarrow\theta-\eta\nabla_{\theta}L(\theta,\overbar{\theta}^{-})$ ;   
10: $\theta^{-}\leftarrow\mu(k)\theta^{-}+(1-\mu(k))\theta$ ;   
11: $k\gets k+1$ ;   
12: until convergence
